Name: Dear Landlord Letter Writer
Subtitle: By Justice Connect
Body text: Dear Landlord can help you if you are struggling to pay rent. Answer a few questions and Dear Landlord will help determine the best way forward, whether that’s helping you draft a rent reduction letter to your landlord, contacting Consumer Affairs Victoria to help negotiate a rent reduction, tips for mediation, or for appearing at VCAT.

Name: Housing.vic Rent  relief grants
Subtitle: Housing.vic
Body text: The Victorian Government has recently announced rent relief grants for Victorians experiencing rental hardship as a result of the coronavirus (COVID-19) crisis.

Name: Consumer Affairs Vic - Tenancy Rights
Subtitle: Consumer Affairs Vic
Body text: Here you’ll find out about rights and responsibilities in areas Consumer Affairs is receiving increased enquiries about, including housing, and products and services.

Name: NSW Tenants Union
Subtitle: NSW Tenants Union
Body text: The Renters' Guide to COVID-19 has been developed to provide legal information about situations that may arise as a result of the COVID-19 pandemic.
Notes: not sure if you are looking for COVID specific things, or if this is just creating headaches with outdated content...

Name: NSW Tenants Union
Display Title: Help to request a rental reduction
Subtitle: NSW Tenants Union
Body text: Find letter templates that can be adapted to your personal circumstances and used to write to your landlord/agent to request a rent reduction due to the financial impacts of COVID-19.
Notes: this is a direct link to a forms part of the same website as above

Name: Tenants Queensland
Display Title: Free statewide advice service for tenants
Subtitle: Tenants Queensland
Body text: Tenants Queensland provides a range of tenancy information and advocacy services including: a statewide telephone advice service for tenants, tenancy publications, a tenancy law training program, and tenancy law research and policy development.

Name: Legal Aid ACT - Tenancy Information
Subtitle: Legal Aid ACT
Body text: Tenancy Advice Service ACT helps renters to understand and assert their legal rights and responsibilities under the Residential Tenancies Act 1997 (ACT) and to identify, address or prevent legal problems before they escalate into more significant matters.

Name: Darwin Community Legal Centre Tenancy info
Subtitle: Darwin Community Legal Service
Body text: The Tenants’ Advice Service (TAS) is an NT-wide, community-based advice and advocacy service for residential tenants.

Name: Rent Right SA
Subtitle: RentRight SA
Body text: RentRight SA is a free, independent service, helping people maintain their tenancies in private rental, community housing or public housing.

Name: Tenancy Union Tasmania
Subtitle: Tenancy Union Tasmania
Body text: The Tenants’ Union of Tasmania is a specialist Community Legal Centre for residential tenants. Their aim is to secure the rights of all tenants by providing free legal advice, representation and education, as well as advocating for the improvement of tenants’ rights.

Name: WA Tenancy support
Subtitle: Tenancy WA Community Legal Centre
Body text: Protecting the right to housing for all tenants through advocacy, advice and education. Tenancy WA helps people who rent their home to resolve their tenancy problems.

Name: Moneysmart calculator
Subtitle: By moneysmart.gov.au
Body text: moneysmart helps Australians take control of their money and build a better life with free tools, tips and guidance

Name: National Debt Helpline
Subtitle: National Debt Helpline
Body text: National Debt Helpline is a not-for-profit service that helps people tackle their debt problems. Their professional financial counsellors offer a free, independent and confidential service.

Name: Australian Banking Association
Display Title:
How to
  get help from your bank
Subtitle: Australian Banking Association
Body text: Here you'll find out about the major changes banks have introduced to help customers through this difficult time.

Name: SA Community  copy
Subtitle: Infoxchange
Body text: Find support services and community groups in South Australia.

Name: Australian Energy Regulator
Subtitle: Australian Energy Regulator
Body text: Sometimes things happen in life that make it hard to pay your bills. Learn about help retailers must provide and what you can do if you have trouble paying your energy bill

Name: Emergency Relief and Food Access Service
Display Title: Help to identify and apply for emergency relief
Subtitle: Provided by the Financial Counselling Network
Body text: The free-call Emergency Relief and Food Access Service is here to support you in identifying and applying for emergency relief. You call call .... or make an online enquiry here https://www.financialcounsellingnetwork.org.au/emergency-relief-and-food-access-service/

Name: Types of food support page
Subtitle: By Ask Izzy
Body text: If you're having trouble feeding yourself or your family, help is available. This page describes some of the common types of food support, and tells you where you can find them.

Name: Study Melbourne community food relief directory
Subtitle: Study Melbourne
Body text: Study Melbourne has collected a list of food and other community supports across Victoria, including services for those on Student or other categories of Visa

Name: City of Melbourne community food guide
Subtitle: City of Melbourne
Body text: Supporting people in the City of Melbourne to access, grow and use healthy food (PDF).

Name: SA Community
Subtitle: Infoxchange
Body text: Find support services and community groups in South Australia.

Name: Emergency Relief and Food Access Service
Display Title: Help to identify and apply for emergency relief
Subtitle: Provided by the Financial Counselling Network
Body text: The free-call Emergency Relief and Food Access Service is here to support you in identifying and applying for emergency relief. You call call .... or make an online enquiry here https://www.financialcounsellingnetwork.org.au/emergency-relief-and-food-access-service/

Name: Foodbank TAS
Display Title: Help to find places that can offer food
Subtitle: Foodbank Tasmania
Body text: If you are hungry or otherwise in need of assistance please contact us on 03 6274 1052 or send an email to distribution@foodbanktas.org.au for help in locating the nearest organisation in your area.

Name: Lifeline
Subtitle: Lifeline
Body text: It is important that you seek help if you feel you need it. Lifeline is here to offer support to you and listen on 13 11 14, or click below to learn more

Name: Beyond Blue
Display Title:
Coping
  with isolation, staying connected and more
Subtitle: Beyond Blue
Body text: Beyond Blue has a collection of resources to help you manage your mental health during and after the pandemic

Name: Mindspot online support
Display Title:
Online
  support for anxiety and depression
Subtitle: Mindspot
Body text: MindSpot has a number of tools, and fact sheets to help people struggling with poor mental health, including a free telephone counselling service.

Name: Jobs Hub
Subtitle: Dept of Education, Skills and Employment
Body text: The Australian Government has developed a site to help workers impacted by COVID-19.

Name: Job Jumpstart
Display Title: Tips and ideas about jobs and careers
Subtitle: Job Jumpstart
Body text: Job Jumpstart offers resources and activities to help you work out what jobs might suit you. It also provides tips and guidance on writing a résumé, preparing for interviews, choosing a job that suits you and connecting with employers.

Name: Australian Apprenticeships
Display Title: Explore the chance to learn new skills while getting paid
Subtitle: Australian Government
Body text: Australian Apprenticeships are available to anyone of working age and offer you opportunities to learn new skills and be paid in over 500 different jobs - learn more a about how this works

Name: MySkills
Display Title: Explore training options to start or change your career
Subtitle: Australian Government
Body text: Myskills is a national directory of vocational education and training (VET) organisations and courses. Whether you are starting your career, looking to upskill or change direction, myskills can help you explore the skills you need.

Name: Centrelink online Portal
Subtitle: Services Australia
Body text: You can do most of your Centrelink, Medicare and Child Support business online, or by phone self service.

Name: Centrelink info in other languages
Subtitle: Services Australia
Body text: Centrelink provides resources in over 40 languages.

Name: Victoria Emergency Housing Support
Subtitle: Victorian Statewide Homelessness Line
Body text: 1800 825 955 will connect you with someone who can assess your needs. This call may not be free from mobiles. If you are ringing from a mobile you can ask to be called back.

Name: Launch housing crisis support
Subtitle: Launch Housing
Body text: Launch Housing offers Melbournians emergency shelter, crisis accommodation, specialist supports, and rough sleeping services so those at risk can secure a safe home.

Name:
Cohealth
  homeless support services
Subtitle: cohealth
Body text: Knowing what services are available to you when you're homeless or at risk of being homeless is not always easy. Cohealth can help you get the support you need on a short or medium term basis to access housing.

Name: Housing Connect
Subtitle: Housing Connect - Dept of Health Tasmania
Body text:
Housing Connect is a one-stop shop for ALL your housing and support needs. One assessment for everything from emergency accommodation to a long-term home. 
Housing Connect can be contacted 24 hours a day, 7 days a week.

Name: Home Hub
Display Title: Find social and affordable housing in Perth
Subtitle: Home Hub
Body text: The Home Hub offers social and affordable housing in Perth, connecting people with safe, secure homes.
Notes: I think it is Perth only, not statewide

Name: Link2home
Display Title: Homelessness information and referral to services
Subtitle: Link2home
Body text: Link2home is the statewide homelessness information and referral telephone service. It is available 24 hours a day, 7 days a week, every day of the year.
Notes:
this is a NSW FACs service, website also lists Ask Izzy as a place to go
https://www.facs.nsw.gov.au/housing/help/ways/are-you-homeless

Name: Homelessness Gateway
Display Title: Entry point into help with housing
Subtitle: Homelessness Gateway
Body text: Open 24/7, we will assess your situation and work with you to find the best option to suit your needs.

Name: Shelterme
Subtitle: shelterme.org.au
Body text: As the Northern Territory maintains its own directory of housing and other relief services, you may find support services at shelterme.org.au that aren't listed in Ask Izzy.

Name: QLD Gov homeless hotline
Subtitle: Queensland Government
Body text: Homeless Hotline can help you if you are homeless or at risk of becoming homeless. Calls are free (calls from mobiles are charged at applicable rates) and the service operates 24 hours a day, 7 days a week.

Name: Entrypoint Perth
Display Title: Perth and WA housing and homelessness support
Subtitle: Entrypoint Perth
Body text: Entrypoint Perth is the first point of contact for families and individuals experiencing or at risk of homelessness, providing assessment and referrals.

Name: Onelink ACT
Subtitle: Onelink
Body text: OneLink provides information and connections for support services in the ACT, including services for families and young people, and services for people who are experiencing or at risk of homelessness.
